TY  - JOUR
AU  - Couts, Spencer J
AU  - Gonçalves, Andrei S
AU  - Rossi, Andrea
T1  - Unsmoothing Returns of Illiquid Funds
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhae006
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 37
IS  - 7
SP  - 2110
EP  - 2155
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Funds investing in illiquid assets report returns with spurious autocorrelation. Consequently, investors need to unsmooth these funds’ returns when evaluating their risk exposures. We show that funds with similar investments share a common source of spurious autocorrelation not fully resolved by traditional unsmoothing methods and thereby leading to underestimation of systematic risk. Thus, we propose a generalized unsmoothing technique and apply it to hedge funds and private commercial real estate funds. Our method significantly improves the measurement of funds’ risk exposures and risk-adjusted performance, especially for highly illiquid funds. Overall, the average illiquid fund alpha is lower than previously thought. (JEL G11, G12, G23)
Y2  - 8/18/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhae006
ER  - 



