TY  - JOUR
AU  - Giannetti, Mariassunta
AU  - Jotikasthira, Chotibhak
T1  - Bond Price Fragility and the Structure of the Mutual Fund Industry
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhad095
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 37
IS  - 7
SP  - 2063
EP  - 2109
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We conjecture that mutual funds with large shares of outstanding bond issues are more inclined to internalize the negative price spillovers of fire sales and thus sell their holdings in those issues, to a lower extent, when they experience redemptions. We provide evidence consistent with this conjecture and further show that ownership concentration limits bonds’ exposures to flow-induced fire sales. We exploit variation in negative spillovers arising from the Fed’s SMCCF to confirm the economic mechanism and explore our findings’ implications for fund performance and fire-sale spillovers to other funds.
Y2  - 8/18/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhad095
ER  - 



